><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 652<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/28/02 10:44:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Resist at high level</span><hr size=1> Resists are not that bad, and INT gear is plentiful.<br><br>As a 46 Wizard my 'walking around' gear gives me INT 250 with about +175 mana.  When I put on my resist gear, I still have about 200 INT.<br><br>But don't worry about INT, it is NOT that important on a Raid, especially a Dragon Raid.  Why?  Well simply put, you will not likely go OOM before either you or the Dragon is dead.  And after that happes (either way) the Raid is effectively done.<br><br>You are going to have more than enough mana to do your part in most cases.  A big mana pool is of most value while Soloing.  In a group, the rate of Mana return is the limiting factor, not how much you have in total.<br><br>If you are interested in Vox, for example:<br><br>Cloak of the Icebear (20CR)<br>Pair of Plat Peridot Rings (2x10CR)<br>Mammoth Hide Legs (5CR)<br><br>Is a relatively cheap 45CR that is not likely to kill your INT too much.<br><br>Now add in Magician Summoned Items:<br>Elemental Blanket (15CR/FR/MR - Back/Shoulder)<br>Shard of the Core (15CR - Range)<br><br>And you have 75CR to add onto your base resist for Cold. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueliezeroferudin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliezer of Erudin</A> at: 5/28/02 1:54:21 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seeker of Truth</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font col